57:21.996 --> 57:23.496
Hey.

57:23.530 --> 57:25.032
I know where the child is.

57:26.333 --> 57:27.902
Don't do anything you'll regret.

57:36.710 --> 57:38.111
God.

58:43.309 --> 58:45.879
No, no, no.

58:45.913 --> 58:47.347
No.

59:03.297 --> 59:05.197
Hey there.

59:05.231 --> 59:06.867
You need some help?

59:09.971 --> 59:11.505
Are you okay?

59:11.539 --> 59:14.075
Yeah, it happens all
the time. I can fix it.

59:29.789 --> 59:31.792
Ma'am, are you sure you're all right?

59:31.826 --> 59:33.326
Yeah, I got it.

59:47.307 --> 59:49.777
Do we know each other from somewhere, man?

59:56.384 --> 59:58.585
Thank you, sir. We appreciate it.

59:58.619 --> 01:00:01.355
Bobby was just following me
to make sure I got home safe.

01:00:10.063 --> 01:00:11.798
You take care of yourself, ma'am.

01:00:12.867 --> 01:00:14.469
Thank you.

01:00:59.947 --> 01:01:01.248
The gate's shut.

01:01:01.282 --> 01:01:02.950
Wait here.

01:01:59.739 --> 01:02:01.241
Let's go.

01:02:19.460 --> 01:02:21.028
Why did you do it?

01:02:24.364 --> 01:02:26.299
Why'd you kill all those people?

01:02:35.909 --> 01:02:37.377
No.

01:02:39.514 --> 01:02:41.349
Is this him?

01:02:42.483 --> 01:02:44.819
Mr. Six O'Clock?

01:02:49.590 --> 01:02:52.793
Okay, just pull over

01:02:52.827 --> 01:02:55.162
and act like anyone else would.

01:03:12.579 --> 01:03:14.614
Okay, keep driving.

01:03:14.648 --> 01:03:16.951
They're not looking for your car.

01:03:25.025 --> 01:03:27.094
So, what's your husband's name?

01:03:30.164 --> 01:03:31.632
Mac.

01:03:33.067 --> 01:03:35.101
"Big Mac."

01:03:38.039 --> 01:03:41.375
Guess Mac'll be home
in around half an hour.

01:03:45.146 --> 01:03:46.681
No.

01:03:49.849 --> 01:03:51.284
I lied.

01:03:52.719 --> 01:03:55.021
He's not coming home.

01:03:59.126 --> 01:04:00.695
He's dead.

01:04:03.797 --> 01:04:06.599
He was stabbed to death by a drug dealer.

01:04:09.068 --> 01:04:11.639
I should've made him stay home that night.

01:04:12.840 --> 01:04:16.177
If I had, he'd still be alive.

01:04:18.913 --> 01:04:20.614
It's all my fault.

01:04:26.820 --> 01:04:28.456
I miss him.

01:04:55.548 --> 01:04:57.550
They found Wilhelm's truck.

01:05:01.222 --> 01:05:03.290
He slipped through, John.

01:05:53.940 --> 01:05:55.475
Is this you?

01:05:56.943 --> 01:05:58.278
Mmm-hmm.

01:06:05.952 --> 01:06:09.090
You, uh, want any help with that?

01:06:10.123 --> 01:06:11.524
No.

01:06:14.427 --> 01:06:16.463
Anything I can do around here?

01:06:17.965 --> 01:06:19.300
Well...

01:06:20.967 --> 01:06:24.571
You could hang that mirror
over there, if you want.

01:06:28.208 --> 01:06:29.708
You got any, uh, nails?

01:06:29.742 --> 01:06:31.445
It's right behind you.

01:06:48.594 --> 01:06:49.929
This wall, right here?

01:06:49.963 --> 01:06:51.230
Mmm-hmm.

01:07:48.822 --> 01:07:50.391
Real butter.

01:07:57.965 --> 01:07:59.667
You can read it, if you like.

01:08:03.603 --> 01:08:05.271
Okay.

01:08:17.751 --> 01:08:19.353
Out loud.

01:08:23.256 --> 01:08:25.624
"God deserves your best.

01:08:25.658 --> 01:08:27.160
"He shaped you for a purpose,

01:08:27.194 --> 01:08:28.627
"and He expects you to make the most

01:08:28.662 --> 01:08:29.795
"of what you have been given."

01:08:29.828 --> 01:08:31.832
I haven't been given anything.

01:08:36.670 --> 01:08:38.439
You have a son.

01:08:40.573 --> 01:08:42.643
I'm never gonna see him again, am I?

01:08:46.578 --> 01:08:48.314
If you stop what you're
doing and give yourself up,

01:08:48.349 --> 01:08:49.817
maybe you will.

01:08:54.354 --> 01:08:55.854
Keep reading.

01:09:00.792 --> 01:09:02.261
"He doesn't want you to worry about

01:09:02.296 --> 01:09:04.763
"or covet abilities you don't have.

01:09:04.796 --> 01:09:06.732
"Instead, He wants you to focus on talents

01:09:06.765 --> 01:09:08.402
"He has given you to use.

01:09:09.569 --> 01:09:11.103
"When you attempt to serve God

01:09:11.136 --> 01:09:13.807
"in ways you're not shaped to serve..."

01:09:13.841 --> 01:09:15.774
"Fear is a self-imposed prison

01:09:15.809 --> 01:09:17.243
"that will keep you from becoming

01:09:17.278 --> 01:09:19.912
"what God intends for you to be.

01:09:19.947 --> 01:09:24.484
"You must move against it,
and weapons of faith and love.

01:09:24.518 --> 01:09:29.154
"The Bible says 'well-formed
love banishes fear...'"

01:09:29.189 --> 01:09:33.660
"Job said, 'My life drags
by, day after hopeless day.

01:09:33.694 --> 01:09:36.361
"'And I give up, I'm tired of living.

01:09:36.395 --> 01:09:40.098
"'Leave me alone, my life makes no sense.'

01:09:40.131 --> 01:09:42.835
"The greatest tragedy is not death,

01:09:42.868 --> 01:09:45.072
"but life without purpose."

01:09:47.006 --> 01:09:49.075
"We were made to have meaning.

01:09:49.109 --> 01:09:51.377
"A young man in his twenties wrote,

01:09:51.411 --> 01:09:52.745
"'I feel like a failure,

01:09:52.779 --> 01:09:54.246
"'because I'm struggling
to become something

01:09:54.279 --> 01:09:56.716
"'and I don't even know what it is.

01:09:56.750 --> 01:09:59.651
"'All I know how to do is to get by.

01:09:59.685 --> 01:10:01.788
"'Someday, if I discover my purpose,

01:10:01.822 --> 01:10:04.391
"'I'll feel I'm beginning to live.'

01:10:04.425 --> 01:10:07.928
"When life has meaning, you
can bear almost anything.

01:10:07.962 --> 01:10:09.862
"Without it, nothing is bearable."

01:10:09.896 --> 01:10:12.332
When I heard I had a son...

01:10:19.706 --> 01:10:21.675
I had to break out.

01:10:24.778 --> 01:10:26.880
I don't belong in that place.

01:10:29.350 --> 01:10:31.051
When I saw what they
were trying to do to me,

01:10:31.085 --> 01:10:33.487
how that judge was trying to enslave me,

01:10:35.989 --> 01:10:38.624
I went into that courtroom

01:10:38.658 --> 01:10:40.561
and I shot him dead.

01:10:41.628 --> 01:10:43.096
You know what?

01:10:46.266 --> 01:10:47.768
It felt good.

01:10:54.375 --> 01:10:56.777
If I were the one who killed your husband,

01:11:00.146 --> 01:11:01.914
could you forgive me?

01:11:07.954 --> 01:11:09.722
I don't know.

01:11:14.427 --> 01:11:16.162
Maybe God can.

01:11:44.925 --> 01:11:47.794
<i>Hey, it's Ashley. Leave a message.</i>

01:11:47.828 --> 01:11:49.862
Well, I guess you're in the shower.

01:11:49.896 --> 01:11:51.196
Okay, well, we're leaving the house now,

01:11:51.230 --> 01:11:52.898
so please don't be late.

01:11:52.932 --> 01:11:54.700
All right, we'll see you at 9:30 sharp.

01:11:54.734 --> 01:11:56.703
Aunt Kim, come on, can we go?

01:11:56.737 --> 01:12:00.005
Yeah, let's go meet your
mama at the Fashion Show.

01:12:00.039 --> 01:12:02.074
You look so pretty!

01:12:28.502 --> 01:12:30.237
Brian, it's time.

01:12:31.471 --> 01:12:34.339
I have to leave now.

01:12:34.373 --> 01:12:36.710
I can't be late to see my daughter.

01:13:25.125 --> 01:13:26.993
I said, I have to go.

01:13:45.145 --> 01:13:46.880
Okay, I'm leaving.

01:13:49.115 --> 01:13:52.185
Paige needs me. I can't
disappoint her again.

01:14:13.006 --> 01:14:14.574
Wait.

01:14:20.948 --> 01:14:22.816
You'll need this.

01:15:32.819 --> 01:15:34.387
Come on!

01:15:53.239 --> 01:15:55.809
Don't you dare die on me.

01:15:57.610 --> 01:15:59.212
<i>Gwinnett County, 911.</i>

01:15:59.246 --> 01:16:01.312
Yes, my name is Ashley Smith.

01:16:01.346 --> 01:16:03.415
The guy from the courthouse, Brian Nichols,

01:16:03.449 --> 01:16:06.218
he's been holding me hostage
for the past seven hours.

01:16:06.252 --> 01:16:08.088
He just let me go.

01:16:08.122 --> 01:16:09.789
<i>Hold on, let me get
you the hotline number.</i>

01:16:09.823 --> 01:16:14.393
No, this isn't a tip. I
was being held hostage...

01:16:14.427 --> 01:16:17.597
<i>Ma'am, you need to start
from the beginning.</i>

01:16:17.631 --> 01:16:19.731
Brian Nichols is in my apartment,

01:16:19.765 --> 01:16:21.167
Bridgewater Apartments.

01:16:21.201 --> 01:16:22.935
<i>Please hold on.</i>

01:16:25.338 --> 01:16:27.472
<i>Miss Smith, this is Sergeant Evans.</i>

01:16:27.506 --> 01:16:28.773
<i>We have your location.</i>

01:16:28.807 --> 01:16:29.808
<i>Stay where you are,
we're sending a...</i>

01:17:30.703 --> 01:17:33.272
<i>There is a man she is identifying</i>

01:17:33.306 --> 01:17:35.307
<i>as Nichols as being
inside her house.</i>

01:17:35.341 --> 01:17:36.676
<i>Now, once again,</i>

01:17:36.710 --> 01:17:38.244
<i>we do not have independent
confirmation...</i>

01:17:44.952 --> 01:17:47.820
<i>...is talking about a
woman in Duluth, Georgia</i>

01:17:47.854 --> 01:17:50.123
<i>who has called the
local police to say...</i>

01:18:00.266 --> 01:18:01.901
Visual on them, give me 20 feet.

01:18:01.935 --> 01:18:03.537
You two, the second team.

01:18:07.940 --> 01:18:10.442
So you're saying you
didn't know him at all.

01:18:10.476 --> 01:18:12.078
No.

01:18:12.112 --> 01:18:13.612
I didn't.

01:18:13.646 --> 01:18:15.315
So why'd he pick your apartment?

01:18:15.349 --> 01:18:16.949
I don't know.

01:18:16.983 --> 01:18:18.918
Were there any drugs involved?

01:18:20.820 --> 01:18:23.621
Answer the question, yes or no?

01:18:23.655 --> 01:18:26.592
Yeah, there was ice. I didn't do any.

01:18:26.626 --> 01:18:28.560
I don't care what you
did or did not do, ma'am.

01:18:28.594 --> 01:18:30.195
How long ago did Nichols use?

01:18:30.229 --> 01:18:32.231
Um...

01:18:32.265 --> 01:18:34.434
About 4:00 a.m.

01:18:36.368 --> 01:18:38.971
All residents in a two-block radius...

01:18:39.005 --> 01:18:40.940
Paige!

01:18:40.974 --> 01:18:42.842
Paige, stop!

01:18:44.711 --> 01:18:46.479
Stop. Stop!

01:18:51.184 --> 01:18:52.517
<i>They're gonna put a tighter</i>

01:18:52.551 --> 01:18:53.852
<i>circle around the apartment</i>

01:18:53.886 --> 01:18:56.755
<i>where they think
that Nichols may be.</i>

01:18:56.789 --> 01:18:58.658
<i>If it is indeed Brian Nichols</i>

01:18:58.692 --> 01:19:00.125
<i>inside of this lady's house,</i>

01:19:00.159 --> 01:19:01.561
<i>is this going exactly the way</i>

01:19:01.595 --> 01:19:03.228
<i>you had just hoped it would not,</i>

01:19:03.262 --> 01:19:04.997
<i>but that you predicted it might?</i>

01:19:07.699 --> 01:19:09.735
<i>This is the worst case scenario</i>

01:19:09.769 --> 01:19:13.638
<i>as far as perhaps him being
in a house with someone else.</i>

01:19:13.672 --> 01:19:16.275
Sir. The landline to the
apartment's up and running.

01:19:18.479 --> 01:19:19.678
<i>If it's him,</i>

01:19:19.712 --> 01:19:21.780
<i>we've got him located someplace.</i>

01:19:21.814 --> 01:19:24.350
<i>This case is breaking so fast, Alex,</i>

01:19:24.384 --> 01:19:25.685
<i>it's hard to get a breath</i>

01:19:25.719 --> 01:19:27.253
<i>and it moves to a new phase.</i>

01:19:27.287 --> 01:19:28.954
<i>Hello?</i>

01:19:28.988 --> 01:19:31.557
<i>Hello, Brian Nichols?</i>

01:19:31.591 --> 01:19:33.426
This is Lieutenant John Chestnut again.

01:19:33.460 --> 01:19:34.660
<i>The entire area that</i>

01:19:34.694 --> 01:19:36.428
<i>you're showing a shot of right now,</i>

01:19:36.462 --> 01:19:39.398
<i>nobody in, nobody out,
but law enforcement.</i>

01:19:46.338 --> 01:19:47.974
Busy.

01:19:51.543 --> 01:19:54.045
<i>It becomes a road called 141</i>

01:19:54.079 --> 01:19:56.115
<i>which takes you right into Duluth.</i>

01:19:59.985 --> 01:20:02.055
I've got movement.

01:20:05.625 --> 01:20:08.928
Positive I.D. on the suspect.

01:20:08.962 --> 01:20:10.530
Permission to fire.

01:20:12.364 --> 01:20:13.331
<i>This individual,</i>

01:20:13.365 --> 01:20:14.801
<i>Mr. Nichols, sounds like</i>

01:20:14.835 --> 01:20:18.103
<i>he's been somewhat astute
in his observations.</i>

01:20:18.137 --> 01:20:21.240
<i>It sounds to me like he has
stayed off main roads...</i>

01:20:29.682 --> 01:20:31.217
<i>It's very accurate.</i>

01:20:31.251 --> 01:20:32.750
<i>We've got Meredith MacKenzie</i>

01:20:32.784 --> 01:20:36.422
<i>joining us now, reporting live
from Bridgewater Apartments.</i>

01:20:36.456 --> 01:20:38.825
<i>The manhunt during the last 24 hours</i>

01:20:38.859 --> 01:20:40.692
<i>has kept the people
of Atlanta in fear</i>

01:20:40.726 --> 01:20:42.962
<i>from a killer with no conscience.</i>

01:20:44.363 --> 01:20:45.966
He's shooting, take cover!

01:20:47.367 --> 01:20:48.668
What's going on?

01:20:48.702 --> 01:20:50.837
Okay, ma'am, I need you to stay back.

01:20:50.871 --> 01:20:52.170
<i>Brian Nichols!</i>

01:20:52.204 --> 01:20:54.106
<i>Put down your weapon
and come out of there</i>

01:20:54.140 --> 01:20:56.642
<i>with your hands in the air.</i>

01:20:56.676 --> 01:21:00.112
<i>Repeat, come out of there
with your hands in the air!</i>

01:21:00.146 --> 01:21:02.247
All rifles, maintain positions!

01:21:18.731 --> 01:21:20.600
<i>Brian Nichols.</i>

01:21:20.634 --> 01:21:22.534
<i>Time to end this.</i>

01:21:22.568 --> 01:21:24.703
<i>Come out, and give yourself up.</i>

01:21:24.737 --> 01:21:28.408
<i>You're completely surrounded,
no way of winning.</i>

01:21:28.442 --> 01:21:30.476
<i>No need to prolong this situation.</i>

01:21:46.726 --> 01:21:49.194
Go get that Smith woman.
Maybe she could talk him out.

01:22:13.819 --> 01:22:15.387
<i>Sorry I can't come to
the phone right now.</i>

01:22:15.421 --> 01:22:18.990
<i>Leave a message. I will get
back to you as soon as I can.</i>

01:22:19.024 --> 01:22:20.426
Lynn.

01:22:20.460 --> 01:22:22.162
It's Brian.

01:22:24.863 --> 01:22:27.533
I wanted to leave a
message for my little boy.

01:22:27.567 --> 01:22:30.069
For Christopher.

01:22:30.103 --> 01:22:32.405
Please don't erase it.

01:22:32.439 --> 01:22:34.473
Please let him...

01:22:34.507 --> 01:22:38.377
Let him listen to it, when he's old enough.

01:22:38.411 --> 01:22:40.680
Christopher, it's your daddy.

01:22:42.782 --> 01:22:45.351
You're gonna hear some bad things about me.

01:22:47.087 --> 01:22:49.422
But, whatever happens,

01:22:49.456 --> 01:22:51.824
whatever people say, I
just want you to know...

01:22:53.193 --> 01:22:54.793
I love you.

01:22:59.131 --> 01:23:00.732
Goodbye, little man.

01:23:12.311 --> 01:23:13.612
What do you want me to say?

01:23:13.646 --> 01:23:15.614
Just say whatever you think is best.

01:23:17.951 --> 01:23:20.420
We don't wanna have to
go in there after him.

01:23:26.091 --> 01:23:27.460
<i>Brian.</i>

01:23:29.162 --> 01:23:30.630
<i>It's Ashley.</i>

01:23:34.167 --> 01:23:35.802
<i>I came back.</i>

01:23:40.939 --> 01:23:43.242
<i>It's not too late, Brian.</i>

01:23:48.148 --> 01:23:49.582
<i>Brian!</i>

01:23:51.751 --> 01:23:53.920
<i>There is purpose in your life.</i>

01:23:56.288 --> 01:23:57.789
<i>It's time.</i>

01:24:01.493 --> 01:24:03.595
<i>Do the right thing, Brian.</i>

01:24:22.381 --> 01:24:24.250
Thank you for trying.

01:24:25.451 --> 01:24:27.487
Get her to a safe place.

01:24:28.688 --> 01:24:30.323
Officer.

01:24:43.836 --> 01:24:46.172
<i>Okay, Brian, it's over.</i>

01:24:46.206 --> 01:24:47.707
<i>Last chance!</i>

01:24:48.841 --> 01:24:51.211
<i>You got exactly 30 seconds!</i>

01:25:19.939 --> 01:25:21.740
He's coming out!

01:25:21.774 --> 01:25:24.076
Hands in the air! Keep it up in the air!

01:25:24.110 --> 01:25:25.276
- Do you see him?
- Affirmative.

01:25:25.310 --> 01:25:26.344
Request permission to fire.

01:25:26.378 --> 01:25:27.745
Stand down!

01:25:27.779 --> 01:25:29.281
Nowhere to go, pal!

01:25:29.315 --> 01:25:31.551
- Show your hands!
- Go, move!

01:25:31.585 --> 01:25:34.053
Go, let's go! Move it, move it!

01:25:34.087 --> 01:25:35.686
- In position, right side!
- Faster, come on!

01:25:35.720 --> 01:25:37.422
No civilians behind the building!

01:25:40.894 --> 01:25:43.361
- He's coming out!
- I don't have a visual!

01:25:43.395 --> 01:25:45.798
Come closer, keep walking!

01:25:45.832 --> 01:25:47.132
Keep walking!

01:25:47.166 --> 01:25:49.234
- Get on your knees!
- Get on your knees!

01:25:49.268 --> 01:25:51.736
Get on your knees! Get on your knees!

01:25:51.770 --> 01:25:52.804
On your knees, on your knees!

01:25:52.838 --> 01:25:53.873
Hands behind your head!

01:25:53.907 --> 01:25:55.007
Let's go!

01:25:55.041 --> 01:25:56.275
Get on the ground, now!

01:25:56.309 --> 01:25:57.910
Don't move!

01:25:57.944 --> 01:25:59.111
- Stay down!
- Eyes down!

01:25:59.145 --> 01:26:00.512
Stay down!

01:26:06.019 --> 01:26:07.619
- Get him up, get him up!
- He's clean.

01:26:46.958 --> 01:26:49.495
Team leaders, let's have them check in.

01:27:29.534 --> 01:27:30.970
Ms. Smith...

01:27:33.706 --> 01:27:36.109
I don't know what you went
through in there, ma'am.

01:27:37.176 --> 01:27:39.878
But whatever you did,

01:27:39.912 --> 01:27:41.546
thank you.

01:28:00.498 --> 01:28:03.568
I'm sorry, ma'am, but you can't go in.

01:28:36.903 --> 01:28:39.204
Mommy!

01:28:39.238 --> 01:28:40.673
Paige!

01:28:42.408 --> 01:28:44.743
Ashley!

01:28:44.777 --> 01:28:47.044
I love you so much!

01:28:47.078 --> 01:28:48.646
Darling, are you okay?

01:28:48.680 --> 01:28:50.215
I am now.

01:28:52.318 --> 01:28:53.985
You came.

01:28:54.019 --> 01:28:55.521
Of course we came.

01:28:58.957 --> 01:29:01.826
I'm sorry I wasn't there this morning.

01:29:01.860 --> 01:29:04.162
But from now on, I will be, okay?

01:29:05.564 --> 01:29:07.665
Just you and me.

01:29:07.699 --> 01:29:09.701
I love you.

01:29:09.735 --> 01:29:11.103
I love you, too.

01:29:14.840 --> 01:29:16.641
Oh, thank God.

01:30:13.466 --> 01:30:15.267
I was very nervous. I was scared.

01:30:15.301 --> 01:30:17.436
What have you just done?

01:30:17.470 --> 01:30:19.771
You have just offered the thing

01:30:19.805 --> 01:30:21.272
that has ruined your life

01:30:21.306 --> 01:30:24.109
and made you crazy to a killer.

01:30:24.143 --> 01:30:26.913
- You're dead now.
- Mmm-hmm.

01:30:29.547 --> 01:30:32.918
Yeah, when I read that, I thought, well...

01:30:32.952 --> 01:30:35.121
Jesus loves you, girl.

01:30:36.756 --> 01:30:39.191
Jesus be looking at you.

01:30:39.225 --> 01:30:43.794
Because, to offer crystal
meth to a killer is pretty...

01:30:43.828 --> 01:30:45.864
I thought, I would rather die

01:30:45.898 --> 01:30:48.333
in this apartment tonight,
not doing those drugs.

01:30:48.367 --> 01:30:49.868
I don't care what happens to me

01:30:49.902 --> 01:30:52.870
as long as I make it out of
here alive to see my daughter.

01:30:52.904 --> 01:30:54.405
Were you at that point thinking,

01:30:54.439 --> 01:30:57.308
"I might be able to
live. I think I can live"?

01:30:57.342 --> 01:30:59.844
I was trying to have some hope, yeah.

01:30:59.878 --> 01:31:00.846
He's here, and he wants
to meet you in person.

01:31:00.880 --> 01:31:02.646
No way.

01:31:02.680 --> 01:31:04.016
Please welcome the author of
<i>The Purpose Driven Life,</i>

01:31:04.050 --> 01:31:05.084
Rick Warren.

01:31:16.494 --> 01:31:19.164
Oprah, there are two great
stories in Ashley's life.

01:31:19.198 --> 01:31:20.598
One of them is,

01:31:20.632 --> 01:31:22.700
you don't have to be
perfect to be used by God.

01:31:22.734 --> 01:31:24.636
Yeah.

01:31:24.670 --> 01:31:26.036
If God only used perfect people,

01:31:26.070 --> 01:31:27.338
nothing would get done,

01:31:27.372 --> 01:31:28.574
because none of us are perfect.

01:31:28.608 --> 01:31:30.342
I think the other thing is that

01:31:30.376 --> 01:31:32.110
no matter how bad your problems are,

01:31:32.144 --> 01:31:34.012
God's purpose is bigger.

01:31:34.046 --> 01:31:36.048
I think it was Ashley's attitude

01:31:36.082 --> 01:31:37.382
from the whole book

01:31:37.416 --> 01:31:38.984
that actually made the difference,

01:31:39.018 --> 01:31:41.786
in that, everybody's looking for hope.

01:31:41.820 --> 01:31:43.154
Yeah.

01:31:43.188 --> 01:31:44.856
The book's just a book about hope.

01:31:44.890 --> 01:31:47.226
Because when people are
going through a crisis,

01:31:47.260 --> 01:31:48.761
they're looking for hope.

